parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seatbelt pretensioner can cause metal fragments to penetrate the occupant in the event of an accident, leading to serious injury or death.
symptoms: None reported
as the issue is related to a potential failure in the event of an accident.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delay in receiving parts for the recall repair can leave vehicles with potentially faulty seatbelt pretensioners on the road, increasing the risk of serious injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: None reported
as the issue is related to the delay in receiving parts for the recall repair.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The entrapment of a child in a car seat due to a faulty seatbelt can lead to serious injury or death.
symptoms: The seatbelt becomes snagged on the underside of the car seat
and the belt will not retract from the retractor mechanism
causing the belt to tighten around the child's upper chest and neck.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the forward safety system can cause the cruise control to stop working, and the collision detection system to malfunction, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The "Check Forward Safety System" warning appears on the dashboard
the cruise control stops working
the collision detection system does not report any collisions
and the system is very sensitive and can be triggered by minor incidents.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to catch fire, which can lead to serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle catches fire
and the cause is assumed to be electrical.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the horn can cause a safety hazard, as it may not alert other drivers or pedestrians, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: The horn stops working
and the issue is intermittent.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended acceleration of the vehicle can cause loss of control, accidents, or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly accelerates
and the cruise control fails.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the HEV system can cause the engine to shut down, and the vehicle to lose power, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The HEV warning light comes on
the engine shuts down
and the vehicle loses power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the integrated thermal management module can cause engine damage, coolant leaks, or even fires, which can lead to serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The check engine light comes on
and the module is diagnosed as faulty.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the backup camera can cause accidents or injuries, as the driver may not be able to see obstacles behind the vehicle.
symptoms: The backup camera stops working
and the issue is intermittent.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The damage to the wiring caused by squirrels can cause electrical system failures, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The wiring is damaged
and the vehicle experiences electrical system failures.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Power Steering and Safety Feature Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering and safety features can cause loss of control, accidents, or injuries.
symptoms: The power steering fails
and most safety-related features stop working.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition coil can cause the engine to lose power, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine revs up
and the car lunges forward
causing the driver to lose control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries. It can also lead to a sudden increase in speed, making it difficult to stop the vehicle, especially in heavy traffic or pedestrian areas.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates suddenly and unexpectedly
often without pressing the accelerator pedal
or continues to accelerate despite pressing the brake pedal. In some cases
the vehicle may lunge forward or jerk suddenly.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Failure of Forward Collision Warning and Safety Systems
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of forward collision warning and safety systems can increase the risk of accidents, injuries, and fatalities. It can also lead to a loss of confidence in the vehicle's safety features.
symptoms: The forward collision warning system fails to alert the driver of potential collisions
or the system disables itself
rendering the cruise control feature inoperable. In some cases
the system may provide false warnings or malfunction intermittently.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Erratic acceleration and deceleration can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries. It can also lead to a sudden increase or decrease in speed, making it difficult to maintain a safe distance from other vehicles.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates or decelerates erratically
often without warning
or fails to respond to accelerator pedal input. In some cases
the vehicle may jerk or lunge suddenly
or the engine may rev unexpectedly.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Traction Control and ABS System Malfunction
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the traction control and ABS systems can increase the risk of accidents, injuries, and fatalities. It can also lead to a loss of vehicle control, especially in adverse weather conditions.
symptoms: The traction control light flickers on and off
accompanied by a loud noise
and the pedals may become stiff or jerky. In some cases
the vehicle may experience sudden and unexpected movements.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the horn can lead to a serious safety concern, as it is an essential feature for warning other drivers, pedestrians, or animals of potential danger.
symptoms: The horn stops working
with no warning or indication beforehand.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unpredictable acceleration and braking can cause accidents, especially when the vehicle surges forward at high speed or comes to a sudden stop.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates or brakes unexpectedly
sometimes without warning
and can feel like the brakes are being overpowered.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Wireless Connectivity Issues with Apple CarPlay and Android Auto
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The frequent disconnection of wireless connectivity can cause distractions while driving, leading to potential accidents.
symptoms: The wireless connection drops repeatedly
requiring the driver to reconnect
and can cause the screen to black out for extended periods.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Forward Collision Warning and Automatic Braking System Malfunction
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunctioning of the forward collision warning and automatic braking system can lead to accidents, especially when the system engages unnecessarily.
symptoms: The system engages repeatedly
even when there is no apparent danger
and can cause the vehicle to brake suddenly.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Sudden Loss of Power and Engine Stalling
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden loss of power and engine stalling can cause accidents, especially when the vehicle is in motion.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly turns off
sometimes without warning
and can restart only to fail again.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering system can cause loss of control, leading to accidents.
symptoms: The steering wheel locks
making it difficult or impossible to steer the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the forward collision sensor can cause the forward collision warning system and adaptive cruise control system to malfunction, leading to potential accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The "Check Forward Safety System" and "Check Smart Cruise Control System" warning messages appear on the dashboard
the forward collision warning system and adaptive cruise control system fail to function
the system suddenly stops working while driving
the system malfunctions despite software updates and recalibration.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Intermittent Forward Collision Warning System Malfunction
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent malfunction of the forward collision warning system can cause false alarms or failure to alert the driver of potential collisions, leading to potential accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The forward collision warning system engages unnecessarily
the system fails to alert the driver of potential collisions
the system malfunctions despite software updates and recalibration.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Failure of Forward Collision Warning System to Engage
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the forward collision warning system to engage can lead to accidents or near-misses, as the driver may not be alerted to potential collisions.
symptoms: The forward collision warning system fails to engage in potential collision situations
the system fails to alert the driver of potential collisions.
